{{Quote|When the Vong struck at us, their way had been prepared for them. They had agents already in place, both disguised Yuuzhan Vong and traitors like Viqi Shesh. And after our first encounters with the Yuuzhan Vong, the enemy found there were tens of thousands of people who were willing to collaborate with them in attacking and enslaving their fellow galactic citizens.|[[Kyp Durron]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Ylesia">''[[The New Jedi Order: Ylesia]]''</ref>}}
The '''Peace Brigade''' was a [[Politics/Legends|political]] faction and paramilitary group that opposed the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. It collaborated with the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] during their [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]]. Their symbol was the image of a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Limb/Legends|hand]] and a Yuuzhan Vong hand clasped, as equals. Ironically, in the [[Yuuzhan Vong (language)|Yuuzhan Vong language]], the phrase for ''peace'' was indistinguishable in meaning from the phrase for ''submission''.

==History==
{{Quote|But those guys with Vehn weren't Yuuzhan Vong.''"<br />"''No, they're worse. They think by turning us in they'll get the Yuuzhan Vong to stop their conquest at the planets they have.|[[Valin Horn]] and [[Anakin Solo]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory I: Conquest">''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory I: Conquest]]''</ref>}}
The Peace Brigade was formed by sentients who thought that the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] maintained an apathetic attitude, and later believed the New Republic was not reacting properly to the threat of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]]. They presumed that the Yuuzhan Vong would ultimately win the war; so, the Peace Brigade thought it best to become the allies of the Yuuzhan Vong against the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. In the process of disrupting planetary governments, capturing ranking officials, and turning over Jedi prisoners to the invasion force, the Brigade was only sealing their own fate, for the Yuuzhan Vong had little use for them once the war had reached a conclusion. But, as membership in the Brigade continued to grow and expand beyond the control of their loose governing structure, it was obvious they required a clear, more rigid command structure to continue functioning as a single, cohesive organization.

[[File:Peace_Brigade.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Members of the Peace Brigade herd Yuuzhan Vong slaves on Ord Sedra]]
The planet [[Metalorn/Legends|Metalorn]] was conquered by the Yuuzhan Vong and then became a recruiting place for the Peace Brigade.<ref name="TEGtW-AC">{{SW|url=news/the-essential-guide-to-warfare-authors-cut-part-9-battlfields-of-the-clone-wars|series=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut|text=Part 9: Battlefields of the Clone Wars}}</ref>

After the Yuuzhan Vong drove the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]] out of their former [[Hutt Space/Legends|Space]], [[Ylesia/Legends|Ylesia]] was granted to the Brigade for use as a location of their central headquarters, where it became the unofficial armed forces of the newly established [[Ylesian Republic]]. The hierarchy was simplistic: a single headquartered group, with command branching down into the smaller, independent cells operating furtively throughout the galaxy. In function, the Brigade was an ideological combination of the [[Bothan Spynet/Legends|Bothan Spynet]] and [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]], employing both guerrilla tactics and political manipulation. The Brigade deployed [[Peace Brigade Fleet|its own fleet]], but its most effective weapon was still subtle manipulation of galactic politics, furthering the goals of their alleged allies, the Yuuzhan Vong.

In the later years of the war, the Peace Brigade and various [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]] forces were used as auxiliaries by the [[Yuuzhan Vong empire]], guarding their conquests and defending rear lines from [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] raids.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way">''[[The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way]]''</ref>

When [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]] reappeared, the Yuuzhan Vong forced him to become Commander-in-Chief of the Ylesia by promising not to attack Sal-Solo's homeworld, [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]]. When Ylesia itself was attacked by a joint task force of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] Fleets, once again the Brigade's command and control ability was crippled; and another blow was dealt when Sal-Solo was captured during the battle. But much like the Black Sun and similar clandestine organizations, the Brigade would soon emerge revitalized and revivified, and with new leadership to continue their fight.

By that point, however, [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] at large had realized and accepted the fact that the Yuuzhan Vong had broken their word far too many times to be again trusted with the promise of mercy. Ironically, at the latter stages of the conflict, the Yuuzhan Vong began to use Peace Brigadiers in their slave forces; however, most of the Peace Brigade remained loyal to the Yuuzhan Vong. Several Peace Brigaders were used to guard the [[Caluula/Legends|Caluula]] spaceport in the final year of the conflict, and were later arrested by [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] forces. After the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar]], ranking members of the Peace Brigade were placed on trial for both [[Treason/Legends|treason]] and war crimes.<ref>citation needed</ref>

